            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has softened, add the <strong>sliced</strong> <strong>garlic</strong> and <strong>chilli</strong> <strong>flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) to the pan and cook for a further 1-2 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>tomato stock </strong>and<strong> halved cherry tomatoes </strong>with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and a pinch of <strong>sugar </strong>and cook for 4-5 min or until the tomatoes have completely softened and the sauce has thickened</p><p>Tip: Squash the cherry tomatoes with the back of a spoon to release their juices!</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1692958202206-x200.jpg",
